        "trailText":"<p>Graeme Swann's Facebook exchange with his brother after England lost the third Test to Australia has prompted outrage</p>",
        "headline":"England's Graeme Swann apologises over Ashes defeat rape comment",
        "body":"<p>Graeme Swann's Facebook exchange with his brother after England lost the third Test to Australia has prompted outrage after the spinner compared the Ashes defeat to being \"arse raped\".</p><p>He posted the comment in response to his brother Alec posting that he had enjoyed a night out seeing the band Shed Seven at Northampton's Roadmender venue. \"Rather have been there than being arse raped in Perth!\" Swann replied.</p><p>His message soon reached the public domain and sparked condemnation from rape charities, which called the Nottinghamshire player's actions appalling and demanded an apology. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Swannyg66/status/413478459373936640\">Swann later tweeted</a>: \"Sorry to anyone who was offended by my comments in the papers today. Crass and thoughtless of me in the extreme.\"</p><p>Yvonne Traynor, the chief executive of Rape Crisis, told the Daily Telegraph: \"We are appalled that Graeme Swann equates a cricket match with the devastatingly serious crime of rape. It is the duty of a people in the public eye to make sure that their own distorted views are kept to themselves and not shared with the general public. These comments lack compassion and intelligence and he should apologise to anyone who has suffered from this heinous crime.\"</p><p>Swann has had a poor series in Australia, taking only seven wickets in three defeats, and he had a particularly bad game in Perth, where he was hit for 22 in an over by Shane Watson. That prompted the former England captain Bob Willis to call for him to be dropped.</p><p>The Australian fast bowler Ryan  Harris apologised for a drunken rant  on Twitter after being refused entry  to a party as he celebrated his side's  Ashes success.</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/425341503|2013-12-19T13:23:07Z|a0fba4708e1bc26eb8ebf7eaa2ee9642ba8fc128 -->",
